  "interpretation": "On DTBK at this scale, the fine-tuned LLaMA recovers consumer demand structure that vanilla LLaMA misses entirely (see scatter figures). Classical baselines retain higher aggregate Pearson on per-POI visit mass because n=6028 trips concentrates signal on the head, where popularity-distance models fit well. The LLM excels at handling the long tail of new/unseen POIs (high coverage 0.84) and at capturing per-visit choice (top1/top5)."
